On @realmoney (Take notice!) A Month End Rebalance Could Produce A Large Buy in Equities and A Large Sell in Bonds Over the Next Few Days * Owing to asset allocators response to the massive outperformance in August of bonds over stocks
This is important and helps to explain why I am a bit reluctant to short stocks now. The month to date performance of fixed income (+9%) - that's the strongest returns since August, 2011.
With equities down by over three percent, August is only the nineteenth month in the last 32 years that bonds have outperformed equities by over +10%.

Historically this has resulted in relatively smart gains in stocks over the last three trading sessions of the month (the median gain is +2.46%, more than 10x the average of the last three trading days of all months since 1987 and delivers a positive return over 80% of the time)
